It's been a devastating Easter for the community of Masinenge in Margate. Over 40 families are still reeling from a shack fire that has left them homeless. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It's been a devastating Easter for the community of Masinenge in Margate. READ: Government promises to speed up shack fire relief Over 40 families are still reeling from a shack fire that has left them homeless. It is believed an exploding gas stove started the blaze. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah has more details in the video above.